                  Ʋſe. 
                Seeing we may know Gods good will, determining of us for good;

Pſal. 106. it ſerves, Firſt, to ſtir us up to ſeek this of God, and to mark the voice of his Spirit in our hearts; when we hear the Goſpel, and when we pray to him, and with all to acquaint our ſelves with graces peculiar to the Elect, and prove our ſelves, whether we have them in us.
